  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Establishing standardized validation protocols and encouraging collaboration between computational scientists, sensory researchers, and clinical professionals will help ensure that AI systems perform reliably in applied contexts.",
    "AI-driven sensory research frequently involves collecting and analyzing sensitive consumer information, including sensory preferences, purchase histories, and dietary habits.",
    "This raises significant ethical concerns about privacy and data ownership (Charlebois et al. 2014).",
    "In particular, applications such as disease detection from breath samples may involve processing health-related biometric data, which is highly sensitive and often subject to stricter regulatory scrutiny.",
    "Such data can potentially reveal not only medical conditions but also lifestyle habits or behavioral traits, raising additional concerns about informed consent and data misuse."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This raises significant ethical concerns about privacy and data ownership (Charlebois et al. 2014)."
  ]
}